-- Sappi to Spend Almost $200 Million on Expansions
-- B y   J a n i c e   K e w
-- 2012-08-03T08:20:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-03/sappi-to-spend-almost-200-million-on-expansions-correct-.html
(Corrects allocation of  capital spending  in first
paragraph.)  Sappi Ltd. will spend almost $200
million in its fiscal fourth quarter, mostly on its chemical
cellulose expansion, including conversions at its Cloquet mill,
Chief Executive Officer Ralph Boettger said.  Work at Cloquet is “going well” and the facility is
expected to be operating by the third quarter of 2013, Boettger
said in Johannesburg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Janice Kew in Johannesburg at 
